# Pegasus iframe theme proxy (optional). When set, `GET /api/v1/pegasus/theme-preferences` with
# `Authorization: Bearer <token>` forwards to Pegasus `GET ${PEGASUS_SITE}/api/apps/pegasus2.0`
# using the `Authenticate` header (same as proto Bitácora BFF).
# PEGASUS_SITE=https://your-pegasus-host.example
# PEGASUS_THEME_APPS_PATH=/api/apps/pegasus2.0
# PEGASUS_FETCH_TIMEOUT_MS=10000

# InfluxDB 2.x — when all four are set, "Number of Entities" uses Flux; otherwise fully mocked.
# INFLUX_HOST=https://xxx.influxdata.com
# INFLUX_TOKEN=
# INFLUX_ORG=
# INFLUX_BUCKET=

# Optional: in-memory cache for GET /api/dashboard/tsp-comparison (full JSON). Default 60000 ms. Set 0 to disable.
# DASHBOARD_CACHE_TTL_MS=60000

# Optional overrides:
# INFLUX_ENTITY_RANGE=-3d
# INFLUX_QUERY_TIMEOUT_MS=60000
# Minimum fraction of vehicles (per mapped provider) that must report a label for support=true. Default 0.5.
# EVENT_LABEL_COVERAGE_THRESHOLD=0.5
# INFLUX_PROVIDERS_MEASUREMENT=providers
# Event/alarm expandable metric: `_field`s on `providers` (label=label_count). Default: label_type only.
# To also count localized descriptions (may double-count vs label_type): INFLUX_EVENT_LABEL_FIELDS=label_type,label_dscrptn_es
# Per-TSP overrides for bucket `provider` tags (JSON). Values may be `null` to force unmapped. Every `tsp-*` id from the dashboard has a default in code; omit keys to keep defaults.
# Observe bucket keys in `server/audit-output/providers.json`. Examples (bind only when validated):
# TSP_PROVIDER_SLUGS={"tsp-example":"teltonika","tsp-other":"pegasus-iot-cloud"}
